WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.011 --> 00:00:07.429
[♪ festive music plays]

2
00:00:07.512 --> 00:00:11.224
[narrator] <i>It's Wrexham at Christmas.</i>
<i>everyone's favorite season.</i>

3
00:00:11.307 --> 00:00:14.227
<i>But the fans are worried.</i>
<i>and this is the reason.</i>

4
00:00:14.310 --> 00:00:15.937
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>Whiteman hooks it</i>
<i>across to the far post.</i>

5
00:00:16.021 --> 00:00:20.608
{\an8}<i>Ricochets around. Drilled in!</i>
<i>Preston equalize and it's Armstrong.</i>

6
00:00:20.692 --> 00:00:23.611
{\an8}<i>and Wrexham will be frustrated</i>
<i>to concede like that.</i>

7
00:00:23.695 --> 00:00:25.238
{\an8}[fan 1] Points just get lost
every single week.

8
00:00:25.321 --> 00:00:28.825
[person 1] Wrexham managed to hang on
for their ninth draw in the Championship.

9
00:00:29.409 --> 00:00:33.538
The highest number of draws
by any team in all of the top four tiers.

10
00:00:33.621 --> 00:00:36.750
{\an8}[narrator] <i>Too many losses</i>
<i>and frustrating draws.</i>

11
00:00:36.833 --> 00:00:40.086
<i>While many speculate.</i>
<i>not one knows the cause.</i>

12
00:00:40.170 --> 00:00:43.548
{\an8}[Randall] It was a terrible.
piss-poor performance.

13
00:00:43.631 --> 00:00:46.718
[person 2] A blow for Wrexham tonight.
How do you bounce back?

14
00:00:46.801 --> 00:00:50.096
What a game to knock you out
of the Christmas spirit that was.

15
00:00:50.180 --> 00:00:53.558
[Gilpin] What we're seeing is a team
that isn't quick.

16
00:00:53.641 --> 00:00:56.811
isn't super powerful.
doesn't create chances.

17
00:00:56.895 --> 00:00:58.980
[Griffiths] <i>There's O'Brien.</i>
<i>Wrexham lose the ball.</i>

18
00:00:59.064 --> 00:01:00.440
Oh. fucking hell.

19
00:01:00.523 --> 00:01:03.902
[narrator] <i>So. the lights are low</i>
<i>and the table looks grim.</i>

20
00:01:03.985 --> 00:01:06.613
<i>The glow at the Cae Ras is flickering dim.</i>

21
00:01:06.696 --> 00:01:07.697
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>Nice touch…</i>

22
00:01:07.781 --> 00:01:11.743
{\an8}[narrator] <i>One mistake from Arthur Okonkwo</i>
<i>was louder than all.</i>

23
00:01:11.826 --> 00:01:14.871
<i>And down to 15th Wrexham fall.</i>

24
00:01:15.789 --> 00:01:21.836
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>And that is the final whistle.</i>
<i>and Wrexham throw away a point at Swansea.</i>

25
00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:24.923
[Gilpin] It's just we saw everything bad
about that Wrexham team

26
00:01:25.006 --> 00:01:26.674
in one entire performance.

27
00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:33.473
[narrator] <i>But the beauty of football</i>
<i>when spirits are low…</i>

28
00:01:33.556 --> 00:01:37.435
<i>Is a second chance waiting</i>
<i>beneath fresh fallen snow.</i>

29
00:01:38.061 --> 00:01:41.064
<i>The dragon's not done.</i>
<i>nor the story all told.</i>

30
00:01:41.147 --> 00:01:45.819
<i>As from the winter's dark gray</i>
<i>may come bright New Year's gold.</i>

31
00:01:47.237 --> 00:01:50.365
♪ <i>Don't forget where you came from </i>♪

32
00:01:50.448 --> 00:01:53.118
♪ <i>Don't forget what you're made of </i>♪

33
00:01:53.201 --> 00:01:55.995
♪ <i>The ones who were there</i> ♪

34
00:01:56.079 --> 00:01:59.165
♪ <i>When no one else would care</i> ♪

35
00:01:59.249 --> 00:02:02.335
♪ <i>Don't be afraid to cry now </i>♪

36
00:02:02.418 --> 00:02:06.506
♪ <i>Even when the world comes crashing in</i> ♪

37
00:02:08.716 --> 00:02:12.679
♪ <i>Don't forget to sing when you win</i> ♪

38
00:02:17.809 --> 00:02:21.938
♪ <i>Don't forget to sing when you win</i> ♪

39
00:02:24.899 --> 00:02:26.693
[♪ "Carol of the Bells" playing]

40
00:02:28.695 --> 00:02:32.532
[producer] Wrex. All right. mate?
Merry Christmas.

41
00:02:32.615 --> 00:02:35.827
{\an8}It's a Great British
footballing tradition is

42
00:02:35.910 --> 00:02:38.371
{\an8}an absolute shed load of fixtures
around Christmas.

43
00:02:38.454 --> 00:02:39.497
but I bloody love it.

44
00:02:39.581 --> 00:02:41.374
I mean. I just… I love that basically

45
00:02:41.457 --> 00:02:44.669
from sort of around December the 23rd
until January the 2nd.

46
00:02:44.752 --> 00:02:46.087
it's just nonstop football.

47
00:02:46.171 --> 00:02:47.547
Seasons greetings!

48
00:02:48.131 --> 00:02:51.009
[singsongy] Come on. you Reds!

49
00:02:51.092 --> 00:02:52.594
[Jones] Christmas is huge. isn't it?

50
00:02:52.677 --> 00:02:55.305
{\an8}It's like probably my favorite time
of the year for football.

51
00:02:55.889 --> 00:02:57.640
{\an8}[Powles] 'Cause you can get to Christmas
and be 20th.

52
00:02:57.724 --> 00:02:59.058
{\an8}and then get to the end of the year

53
00:02:59.142 --> 00:03:03.271
{\an8}and you can be… [stammers]
…a few points off making the playoffs.

54
00:03:03.354 --> 00:03:04.856
Three wins in a row and…

55
00:03:04.939 --> 00:03:06.858
{\an8}-Everything changes.
-they could be right back in the mix.

56
00:03:06.941 --> 00:03:09.569
{\an8}The holiday period.
four games in ten days.

57
00:03:09.652 --> 00:03:13.323
{\an8}and we've got to come out of that
with a good haul of points

58
00:03:13.406 --> 00:03:16.242
to keep our promotion push in place.

59
00:03:16.326 --> 00:03:19.662
[♪ "Carol of the Bells" continues]

60
00:03:26.961 --> 00:03:30.256
[Okonkwo] This is me in my den.
I don't play as much anymore.

61
00:03:30.340 --> 00:03:33.843
My friends are gonna say. "Yes. you do."
But I don't think I do.

62
00:03:34.594 --> 00:03:36.429
{\an8}At the moment. I'm playing <i>2K26</i>.

63
00:03:38.264 --> 00:03:41.601
I used to be a huge gamer.
<i>Call of Duty</i> was my game.

64
00:03:41.684 --> 00:03:43.728
It's so hard to be a gamer
and play football.

65
00:03:43.811 --> 00:03:45.688
Like… [chuckles] …they don't correlate.

66
00:03:48.149 --> 00:03:49.317
[Okonkwo] Watch TV.

67
00:03:49.400 --> 00:03:51.861
[producer] What. watching
endless football matches? No?

68
00:03:51.945 --> 00:03:53.738
At the moment.
you wanna know what I'm watching?

69
00:03:53.821 --> 00:03:54.864
I'm watching <i>Twilight</i>.

70
00:03:54.948 --> 00:03:57.700
{\an8}[wolf howls]

71
00:03:57.784 --> 00:03:59.702
Which is actually really good.

72
00:03:59.786 --> 00:04:02.038
When we normally play rival teams.

73
00:04:02.121 --> 00:04:04.958
I think there's certain teams
that I don't like.

74
00:04:06.334 --> 00:04:08.962
Can I… Can I even… Oh. no. I shouldn't.

75
00:04:09.045 --> 00:04:10.838
Should I just say the teams I don't like?

76
00:04:11.339 --> 00:04:13.967
[Griffiths] <i>Welcome to Swansea.</i>

77
00:04:16.219 --> 00:04:18.471
{\an8}<i>Tipped over well by Okonkwo.</i>

78
00:04:18.554 --> 00:04:19.889
I was having a really good game.

79
00:04:19.973 --> 00:04:22.725
[Griffiths] <i>An inswinger. left-footed</i>
<i>again. swept to the far post.</i>

80
00:04:22.809 --> 00:04:24.852
<i>Okonkwo comes. takes that comfortably.</i>

81
00:04:24.936 --> 00:04:28.398
<i>But it will fall for a shot.</i>
<i>which Okonkwo gets right behind.</i>

82
00:04:28.481 --> 00:04:30.316
<i>Free kick on the halfway line.</i>

83
00:04:31.067 --> 00:04:34.153
<i>Okonkwo's coming.</i>
<i>and punches. rather up in the air.</i>

84
00:04:34.237 --> 00:04:36.948
<i>It's headed into the goalmouth.</i>
<i>Okonkwo goes back.</i>

85
00:04:37.031 --> 00:04:39.033
<i>Mishandles it! It's a horrible mistake!</i>

86
00:04:39.117 --> 00:04:40.994
<i>Oh. what happened there?</i>

87
00:04:41.077 --> 00:04:44.789
{\an8}[Okonkwo] In the moment. I wanted
the world to just swallow me whole.

88
00:04:44.872 --> 00:04:46.374
{\an8}[Williams] He shouldn't
have come out for it.

89
00:04:46.457 --> 00:04:50.086
{\an8}Mistakes-wise. it was as… pretty
much as bad as they come for a goalkeeper.

90
00:04:50.169 --> 00:04:55.216
[Griffiths] <i>Horrible way to lose a derby.</i>
<i>But what a mistake by Okonkwo.</i>

91
00:04:55.300 --> 00:04:56.801
Obviously. I was fuming.

92
00:04:56.884 --> 00:04:59.971
but you know. I can't…
I can't really show that.

93
00:05:00.805 --> 00:05:03.766
I don't think I'm that type of person
to bring the team down.

94
00:05:03.850 --> 00:05:05.893
like. because I'm feeling
a certain type of way.

95
00:05:07.478 --> 00:05:08.896
{\an8}It's really hard to take.

96
00:05:10.064 --> 00:05:13.818
{\an8}[Parkinson] Young players or any player's
gonna make mistakes. it's how you respond.

97
00:05:13.901 --> 00:05:16.529
{\an8}and Arthur's always got our full support
because he cares a lot

98
00:05:16.612 --> 00:05:20.325
{\an8}and he's been instrumental into getting
Wrexham. you know. into this division.

99
00:05:21.659 --> 00:05:24.162
[Davidson] Get your feet right.
Focus on your contact.

100
00:05:24.787 --> 00:05:26.289
Strike it at them.

101
00:05:26.372 --> 00:05:28.833
-Here we go. Cal. Keep the focus.
-[Okonkwo grunts]

102
00:05:28.916 --> 00:05:30.293
{\an8}Hit him in his nose.

103
00:05:32.170 --> 00:05:33.963
[Williams] It's all about
how he bounces back now.

104
00:05:34.047 --> 00:05:36.591
[Randall] Arthur's save percentage has
been ludicrous.

105
00:05:36.674 --> 00:05:39.719
I think it was up near the 75. 78 mark
last time I looked.

106
00:05:39.802 --> 00:05:42.138
So. he's done…
he's got more credit in the bank.

107
00:05:42.221 --> 00:05:44.599
[Davidson] Get those fucking feet going.

108
00:05:44.682 --> 00:05:46.559
[Randall] I'm glad that
Parky came out afterward

109
00:05:46.642 --> 00:05:48.311
and said.
"Look. he's been a colossus for us.

110
00:05:48.394 --> 00:05:50.897
Let's move past it."
because that's what you've gotta do.

111
00:05:50.980 --> 00:05:52.815
[Williams] Let's just see how he recovers.

112
00:05:58.237 --> 00:06:01.032
{\an8}[customer. in Welsh]

113
00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:09.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

114
00:06:10.041 --> 00:06:14.337
[in English] I'm Maxine. I'm a journalist.
originally from North Wales.

115
00:06:14.420 --> 00:06:16.756
I am based in the United States.

116
00:06:16.839 --> 00:06:21.260
and I'm also the Welsh translator
for Rob and Ryan.

117
00:06:21.344 --> 00:06:22.512
[director] Thank you. Here we go.

118
00:06:22.595 --> 00:06:23.679
[crew member] And mark.

119
00:06:24.514 --> 00:06:27.642
-Hello. my name is Rob McElhenney.
-My name is Ryan Reynolds.

120
00:06:27.725 --> 00:06:29.852
{\an8}[in Welsh]

121
00:06:32.897 --> 00:06:35.400
[in English]
Never. ever say that Wales is in England.

122
00:06:35.483 --> 00:06:37.235
-[Mac] Oh. God.
-Oh. we're aware of that.

123
00:06:37.318 --> 00:06:39.404
-We're very. very. very aware of that.
-We're aware of that.

124
00:06:41.072 --> 00:06:42.824
{\an8}[Hughes in Welsh]

125
00:06:42.907 --> 00:06:45.451
{\an8}[Hughes narrating in English]
I would say being Welsh plays a role

126
00:06:45.535 --> 00:06:46.953
in everything I do.

127
00:06:47.036 --> 00:06:48.830
[Hughes] Yeah.

128
00:06:48.913 --> 00:06:50.998
[Hughes narrating]
Whether it's bringing up my children

129
00:06:51.082 --> 00:06:53.418
and teaching them about Wales
and speaking Welsh to them.

130
00:06:53.501 --> 00:06:56.838
{\an8}[in Welsh]

131
00:06:56.921 --> 00:06:59.382
[in English]
Or my work broadcasting through Welsh.

132
00:06:59.465 --> 00:07:02.385
{\an8}[in Welsh]

133
00:07:02.468 --> 00:07:04.011
[in English] It's very important to me.

134
00:07:04.303 --> 00:07:08.099
{\an8}[in Welsh]

135
00:07:11.436 --> 00:07:13.229
{\an8}[Hughes's partner]

136
00:07:15.398 --> 00:07:16.858
{\an8}[friend]

137
00:07:16.941 --> 00:07:18.526
{\an8}[in English]

138
00:07:22.738 --> 00:07:23.823
Yes.

139
00:07:23.906 --> 00:07:26.909
This is the turning point
in the interview. Duh-duh-duh.

140
00:07:26.993 --> 00:07:28.703
[♪ ominous music plays]

141
00:07:33.875 --> 00:07:38.546
{\an8}[in Welsh]

142
00:07:42.842 --> 00:07:47.096
{\an8}[in English] My initial instinct
when I was diagnosed with cancer

143
00:07:47.180 --> 00:07:49.557
was to pick up a camera and document it.

144
00:07:49.640 --> 00:07:51.726
[breathes deeply]

145
00:07:51.809 --> 00:07:52.894
[sniffles]

146
00:07:54.228 --> 00:07:57.356
When you go through so much trauma
in such a short period of time.

147
00:07:57.982 --> 00:08:00.067
I think it's really hard
to come out of that.

148
00:08:00.151 --> 00:08:05.406
And the people that are there with you
along the way. who support you.

149
00:08:05.490 --> 00:08:09.327
you feel even more grateful for.

150
00:08:09.994 --> 00:08:13.247
-Welsh cakes. So. flour--
-[Bill] What is a Welsh cake?

151
00:08:13.331 --> 00:08:16.876
The Welsh name for Welsh cake is
<i>Pice ar y maen</i>.

152
00:08:16.959 --> 00:08:19.921
And it's kind of like a flat scone.

153
00:08:20.004 --> 00:08:21.047
A scone?

154
00:08:21.130 --> 00:08:22.715
No. it's… it's a scone.

155
00:08:22.798 --> 00:08:25.176
{\an8}-Scone. [chuckles] Flat scone.
-[Hughes] It's a flat scone.

156
00:08:25.259 --> 00:08:28.387
{\an8}Over the years. working closely with Rob.

157
00:08:28.471 --> 00:08:31.766
we've gotten to know each other
and each other's family.

158
00:08:31.849 --> 00:08:35.102
You have to. like. make it
until it's kind of like crumbs.

159
00:08:35.186 --> 00:08:37.563
{\an8}-So. you gave me the dirty job. basically.
-Yes. I did.

160
00:08:37.647 --> 00:08:40.525
{\an8}-You did that very intentionally.
-I know. [laughs]

161
00:08:40.608 --> 00:08:43.444
{\an8}Since meeting Jill. Rob's stepmother.

162
00:08:43.528 --> 00:08:47.490
there's something quite similar
about us. maybe.

163
00:08:47.573 --> 00:08:51.118
Um. I don't know if Jill would like to…
[chuckles] …hear that or not.

164
00:08:51.202 --> 00:08:54.747
How many hands… How many hands can we put
in this Welsh cake?

165
00:08:54.830 --> 00:08:57.416
[Hughes] As soon as I was
diagnosed with cancer.

166
00:08:57.500 --> 00:08:59.877
she was the most obvious person
for me to call

167
00:08:59.961 --> 00:09:02.880
because I knew
that she went through cancer herself.

168
00:09:02.964 --> 00:09:05.007
I think we talked plainly to one another.

169
00:09:05.091 --> 00:09:06.300
-Yes. like directly.
-Right.

170
00:09:06.384 --> 00:09:09.262
When somebody has a diagnosis
that is catastrophic.

171
00:09:09.345 --> 00:09:12.223
and potentially. you know.
life-threatening.

172
00:09:12.306 --> 00:09:15.393
it creates opportunities to really deepen

173
00:09:15.476 --> 00:09:18.479
and create a very intimate relationship
with your support system.

174
00:09:18.563 --> 00:09:19.564
Hang on a second. Here we go.

175
00:09:21.107 --> 00:09:24.694
[Hughes] When I was going through chemo.
and when I was doing all my treatment.

176
00:09:24.777 --> 00:09:28.781
I looked on my phone
and I had an email from the Eisteddfod…

177
00:09:28.864 --> 00:09:30.616
[trumpets playing]

178
00:09:37.081 --> 00:09:40.293
[Hughes] …saying that I was
gonna be inducted into the Gorsedd.

179
00:09:40.376 --> 00:09:41.794
to be made a bard.

180
00:09:41.877 --> 00:09:43.254
[singing in Welsh]

181
00:09:45.381 --> 00:09:47.800
[Hughes] To be invited is…

182
00:09:48.759 --> 00:09:53.681
I guess it would be compared to something
like being knighted in England.

183
00:09:53.764 --> 00:09:59.437
So. I-I was due to have a double
mastectomy. the week of the Eisteddfod.

184
00:09:59.520 --> 00:10:03.399
and I asked the surgeon to delay it
and to move everything.

185
00:10:03.482 --> 00:10:05.109
[Druid speaking Welsh]

186
00:10:05.192 --> 00:10:07.320
…Maxine John Conwy.

187
00:10:07.903 --> 00:10:09.822
[crowd cheering]

188
00:10:11.824 --> 00:10:13.701
[Hughes] It was just so meaningful for me.
you know…

189
00:10:13.784 --> 00:10:18.789
[stutters] …to have this happen to me
during this period of my life.

190
00:10:18.873 --> 00:10:22.918
in this place that has provided
so much positivity

191
00:10:23.002 --> 00:10:25.046
for me and for my children.

192
00:10:26.047 --> 00:10:28.132
[Hughes] Hello. [sniffling]

193
00:10:28.883 --> 00:10:31.052
-How are you?
-I'm feeling good.

194
00:10:31.135 --> 00:10:32.553
{\an8}-Excellent.
-Yeah.

195
00:10:32.637 --> 00:10:34.639
{\an8}So. we have some paperwork to do. I guess.

196
00:10:34.722 --> 00:10:35.931
{\an8}-Yeah. I think so.
-Yeah.

197
00:10:36.015 --> 00:10:37.642
[machine beeping]

198
00:10:38.434 --> 00:10:40.478
[Hughes] When I went
into my oncologist's office.

199
00:10:40.561 --> 00:10:44.106
and she said.
"You don't have cancer anymore.

200
00:10:44.190 --> 00:10:47.610
You had a complete pathological response
to the chemo

201
00:10:47.693 --> 00:10:49.278
and you've had a mastectomy."

202
00:10:49.362 --> 00:10:54.408
And I said. "Wow. what am I supposed now?
'Cause I'm terrified."

203
00:10:54.492 --> 00:10:56.661
And she said.
"You have to go live your life."

204
00:10:57.244 --> 00:10:59.997
And because of relationships
that I've made through Wrexham.

205
00:11:00.081 --> 00:11:03.709
and the support I'd received
from the community of Wrexham.

206
00:11:03.793 --> 00:11:06.962
I feel so excited about new things.

207
00:11:07.713 --> 00:11:11.884
Now. I feel like
I'm exactly where I'm supposed to be.

208
00:11:12.426 --> 00:11:16.514
I guess I just feel like
I've had a second chance.

209
00:11:16.597 --> 00:11:19.392
-[child babbling]
[Hughes] Unbelievable.

210
00:11:19.475 --> 00:11:21.602
[all chattering]

211
00:11:23.437 --> 00:11:26.774
[narrator] <i>With desks adorned</i>
<i>with cheap tinsel and cheer.</i>

212
00:11:26.857 --> 00:11:30.403
<i>The lights that half work.</i>
<i>but come out every year.</i>

213
00:11:30.486 --> 00:11:34.657
So. we have a little competition going on
for best festive workspace area.

214
00:11:34.740 --> 00:11:37.201
-Oh. wow. that's serious.
-[employee] It's cozy. isn't it?

215
00:11:37.284 --> 00:11:40.329
He's also killed Santa Claus
for a Christmas competition.

216
00:11:40.413 --> 00:11:42.748
-[employee 2 laughing]
-Got work to do now. [chuckles]

217
00:11:42.832 --> 00:11:47.878
[Williamson] Oh. 'tis the season.
obviously. 'Tis the season. [chuckles]

218
00:11:47.962 --> 00:11:51.090
[narrator] <i>All of Wrexham was buzzing</i>
<i>with great Christmas spirit.</i>

219
00:11:51.173 --> 00:11:54.760
<i>Then came great news</i>
<i>with everyone happy to hear it.</i>

220
00:11:55.720 --> 00:11:59.682
[Gilpin] Ollie Rathbone has taken
the 25th spot in the squad.

221
00:11:59.765 --> 00:12:00.808
Liam. did we know that?

222
00:12:00.891 --> 00:12:02.977
I-I mean. Parky had mentioned
it was likely to be.

223
00:12:03.060 --> 00:12:04.520
but I don't know that it was confirmed.

224
00:12:04.603 --> 00:12:06.939
So. no. that is exclusive.

225
00:12:07.022 --> 00:12:11.068
{\an8}I think we're on a bit of a rocky run.
we're getting a few draws. and doing okay.

226
00:12:11.152 --> 00:12:13.738
And then we had that kick in the teeth
at Swansea.

227
00:12:13.821 --> 00:12:16.365
It could go either way here.
If you get on a good run. great.

228
00:12:16.449 --> 00:12:19.368
But if it goes the other way. then you're
looking over your shoulder a little bit.

229
00:12:19.452 --> 00:12:20.911
But it's such a tight league. isn't it?

230
00:12:20.995 --> 00:12:23.873
If you get one win.
you're right up that table straight away.

231
00:12:23.956 --> 00:12:26.625
Yeah. I don't think you can kind of get
too high with the good ones

232
00:12:26.709 --> 00:12:28.377
and too low with the bad ones

233
00:12:28.461 --> 00:12:30.921
because the quality
of the division is so high.

234
00:12:31.005 --> 00:12:33.799
I had a really difficult start
to the year.

235
00:12:35.134 --> 00:12:39.054
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>Ollie Rathbone with</i>
<i>five minutes to go in this first half.</i>

236
00:12:39.138 --> 00:12:41.056
<i>Putting Ryan Grant under pressure.</i>

237
00:12:42.057 --> 00:12:43.976
[Rathbone] The ball came to me
on the edge of the box.

238
00:12:44.059 --> 00:12:47.229
I think I chested it down.
we were kind of scrapping for the ball.

239
00:12:47.313 --> 00:12:50.274
And then in the middle of it all.
I just felt a big crack.

240
00:12:50.941 --> 00:12:53.444
Yeah. finding out
that I'd ruptured the ligament.

241
00:12:54.111 --> 00:12:56.572
It was really. really difficult.
I can't lie.

242
00:12:56.655 --> 00:12:58.532
because I also felt
a little bit embarrassed.

243
00:12:58.616 --> 00:13:00.910
Kind of last year being.
like. the Player of the Season.

244
00:13:00.993 --> 00:13:03.078
And then. like. a few months later.
kind of not playing

245
00:13:03.162 --> 00:13:06.248
and not getting on the bench
and being injured.

246
00:13:06.332 --> 00:13:08.167
[Mick] He didn't really say
that much about it.

247
00:13:08.250 --> 00:13:10.127
but I could tell
he was a little bit worried.

248
00:13:10.211 --> 00:13:13.964
{\an8}My name's Mick Rathbone.
I'm Oliver Rathbone's father.

249
00:13:14.048 --> 00:13:15.299
Proud father.

250
00:13:15.841 --> 00:13:18.886
Fifty years in professional football is
my claim to fame.

251
00:13:18.969 --> 00:13:20.971
Predominantly. I played for Blackburn
for seven years.

252
00:13:21.055 --> 00:13:22.181
the bulk of my playing career.

253
00:13:22.264 --> 00:13:24.767
I was physio seven years at Preston.

254
00:13:24.850 --> 00:13:26.811
and then eight years.
I was head of medical at Everton.

255
00:13:26.894 --> 00:13:29.897
But with Oliver. we kind of tried
to get him to do other things.

256
00:13:29.980 --> 00:13:31.899
but he always came back to football.

257
00:13:33.567 --> 00:13:35.027
He slept with a football.

258
00:13:35.110 --> 00:13:37.822
I'll pull onto the drive.
and every single day.

259
00:13:37.905 --> 00:13:40.783
there he was stood there
with the ball under his arm.

260
00:13:40.866 --> 00:13:44.954
and I couldn't go in until we played shots
in the front garden.

261
00:13:45.037 --> 00:13:48.249
And he had to score ten goals
with his left. ten goals with his right.

262
00:13:48.332 --> 00:13:51.085
Then I found out when I was a lot older.
he used to. like. sometimes park

263
00:13:51.168 --> 00:13:53.712
at the bottom of the road
and wait for it to go dark.

264
00:13:53.796 --> 00:13:56.340
"No. I can't play now. Son. It's dark."
[chuckles]

265
00:13:58.300 --> 00:14:00.845
How frustrating is it.
when you've done all pre-season…

266
00:14:00.928 --> 00:14:02.763
-Mmm.
-…fit as a fiddle. good to go. raring.

267
00:14:02.847 --> 00:14:04.348
And then you get that injury.
and you're out of the team

268
00:14:04.431 --> 00:14:05.432
for the next three. four months.

269
00:14:05.516 --> 00:14:07.017
I came up from Australia

270
00:14:07.101 --> 00:14:09.854
but by the time I'd got fit.
we'd signed Josh Windass. Lewis O'Brien.

271
00:14:09.937 --> 00:14:12.147
Nathan Broadhead. Ben Sheaf.

272
00:14:12.857 --> 00:14:15.776
We basically signed five players
that could play in my position.

273
00:14:15.860 --> 00:14:18.445
You do kind of worry like.
"Oh. if I don't get back playing.

274
00:14:18.529 --> 00:14:20.447
then maybe I'll have to go on loan
in January

275
00:14:20.531 --> 00:14:22.157
or get some game time elsewhere."

276
00:14:22.783 --> 00:14:24.869
Like. the whole group was
kind of. like. getting together.

277
00:14:24.952 --> 00:14:27.288
and they were all getting
to know each other and training together.

278
00:14:27.371 --> 00:14:29.373
and I was kind of just. like.
a spare part. [chuckles]

279
00:14:29.456 --> 00:14:32.209
Just. like. waiting to get back involved.

280
00:14:32.293 --> 00:14:34.461
For your whole life. you say.
"Oh. I'm a footballer."

281
00:14:34.545 --> 00:14:36.171
When you're injured.
you don't feel like that.

282
00:14:37.339 --> 00:14:40.551
[Ker] I think it's quite hard
for people outside of football

283
00:14:40.634 --> 00:14:42.928
to understand
how psychologically damaging an injury is

284
00:14:43.012 --> 00:14:48.517
because it is… [stammers] …a player's
entire sense of self and being.

285
00:14:49.018 --> 00:14:50.936
And while you're recovering
from an injury.

286
00:14:51.020 --> 00:14:53.147
you're watching the guy
who's playing in your position.

287
00:14:53.230 --> 00:14:54.857
he's doing very well.
and you're wondering.

288
00:14:54.940 --> 00:14:56.942
"Am I ever gonna get
to dislodge that player?

289
00:14:57.026 --> 00:14:58.611
Am I gonna get to be part of this?"

290
00:14:59.695 --> 00:15:03.365
It's hard to kind of keep positive and…
all the time.

291
00:15:03.449 --> 00:15:04.992
You just gotta kind of keep the faith

292
00:15:05.075 --> 00:15:07.661
that you're gonna get your opportunity
at some point.

293
00:15:07.745 --> 00:15:10.164
and when you do.
you just gotta make sure you're ready.

294
00:15:11.373 --> 00:15:13.500
{\an8}[crowd cheering]

295
00:15:15.502 --> 00:15:17.296
Yeah. Ollie. Ollie.

296
00:15:17.379 --> 00:15:19.715
[Rathbone] Everyone's saying.
"Oh. you'll get your chance."

297
00:15:19.798 --> 00:15:22.134
But then. it's very much… [chuckles]
…down to you to take your chance.

298
00:15:22.217 --> 00:15:24.428
You know. if he gives you a chance.
and you don't take it.

299
00:15:24.511 --> 00:15:26.597
then you are really on the back foot.

300
00:15:27.389 --> 00:15:29.934
[Griffiths] Big round of applause
for Rathbone.

301
00:15:30.017 --> 00:15:34.355
{\an8}whose injuries. of course. have limited
his chances. comes onto the pitch.

302
00:15:34.438 --> 00:15:35.814
[crowd chanting] Ollie! Ollie!

303
00:15:35.898 --> 00:15:37.566
Windass with the away swinger.

304
00:15:37.650 --> 00:15:42.363
Steps up. stands it beyond the far post.
a great header by Pollock.

305
00:15:42.446 --> 00:15:46.784
Rathbone. edge of the area.
In for the shot! Rathbone scores!

306
00:15:46.867 --> 00:15:50.788
The hummingbird strikes! Oh. what a hit!

307
00:15:50.871 --> 00:15:52.456
What a story!

308
00:15:52.998 --> 00:15:54.041
♪ <i>Guess who's back</i> ♪

309
00:15:54.124 --> 00:15:56.001
♪ <i>Guess who's back</i> ♪

310
00:15:56.585 --> 00:15:57.962
{\an8}♪ <i>Guess who's back</i> ♪

311
00:15:58.045 --> 00:15:59.880
{\an8}♪ <i>The king is back. whoa</i> ♪

312
00:16:00.673 --> 00:16:02.174
I was just so happy.

313
00:16:03.133 --> 00:16:05.511
Just pure. pure joy.

314
00:16:05.594 --> 00:16:07.721
And yeah.
just not looked back since. really.

315
00:16:08.514 --> 00:16:11.558
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>Wrexham</i>
<i>against Preston North End.</i>

316
00:16:11.642 --> 00:16:13.394
{\an8}<i>Broadhead. He's got Thomason outside him.</i>

317
00:16:13.477 --> 00:16:18.315
{\an8}<i>Inside to Dobson now. 25 yards out.</i>
<i>Plays the killer ball! Rathbone!</i>

318
00:16:18.399 --> 00:16:20.109
♪ <i>This is a moment of greatness</i> ♪

319
00:16:20.192 --> 00:16:21.777
♪ <i>Championship. how I played it</i> ♪

320
00:16:21.860 --> 00:16:24.655
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>The super sub strikes again.</i>

321
00:16:24.738 --> 00:16:27.032
{\an8}Ollie's return to size has
been enormously exciting.

322
00:16:27.116 --> 00:16:29.576
He's brought energy.
He's brought dynamism.

323
00:16:29.660 --> 00:16:34.373
He's brought his patented 4'4" rascalness.

324
00:16:34.456 --> 00:16:38.168
I don't know how tall… Everyone's about
the same height to me when I look down.

325
00:16:38.252 --> 00:16:41.839
{\an8}Wrexham. at Blackburn Rovers.
looking to build

326
00:16:41.922 --> 00:16:44.591
on those two excellent home performances.

327
00:16:44.675 --> 00:16:47.511
And then Ollie Rathbone's dad is
a legend here.

328
00:16:47.594 --> 00:16:50.389
Mick Rathbone is
having a presentation today.

329
00:16:50.472 --> 00:16:54.727
One of three players who have been brought
into their equivalent of the Hall of Fame.

330
00:16:54.810 --> 00:16:57.771
[Roberts] And I think Ollie Rathbone…
Well. what's he played so far this season?

331
00:16:57.855 --> 00:17:00.983
About ten minutes in the Championship
and already got two goals to his name.

332
00:17:01.066 --> 00:17:03.861
Ollie's class.
I missed him all season to be fair.

333
00:17:04.361 --> 00:17:06.989
Love him.
Didn't get to see Mickey Thomas play. but…

334
00:17:07.072 --> 00:17:09.366
Maybe it's just the hair.
but shades of Mickey Thomas. I think.

335
00:17:09.450 --> 00:17:10.617
got a goal in him.

336
00:17:10.701 --> 00:17:13.495
[Griffiths] <i>Rathbone intercepts</i>
<i>and now goes scurrying forward.</i>

337
00:17:13.579 --> 00:17:14.580
<i>Only Longman ahead of him.</i>

338
00:17:14.663 --> 00:17:16.957
<i>He's taken late.</i>
<i>and that's gonna be a card.</i>

339
00:17:17.041 --> 00:17:21.045
<i>Free kick. Matty James is on it.</i>
<i>Little run behind the line by Hyam.</i>

340
00:17:21.128 --> 00:17:22.755
<i>It's swept in across the bodies.</i>

341
00:17:22.838 --> 00:17:24.840
<i>and will drop for Rathbone</i>
<i>who hooks it in.</i>

342
00:17:24.923 --> 00:17:26.300
<i>Oh! What a goal!</i>

343
00:17:26.383 --> 00:17:31.388
{\an8}<i>At the ground that his dad</i>
<i>served Blackburn with such quality.</i>

344
00:17:31.472 --> 00:17:33.182
{\an8}<i>His son nails it!</i>

345
00:17:33.265 --> 00:17:36.018
[crowd cheering]
Ollie! Ollie! Ollie! Ollie!

346
00:17:36.101 --> 00:17:38.896
The crowd is singing my name. and
I'm looking up at my mom and dad. like…

347
00:17:38.979 --> 00:17:40.773
trying hard for like.
my lip not to quiver…

348
00:17:40.856 --> 00:17:42.441
and kind of not to well up. because…

349
00:17:42.524 --> 00:17:43.901
it was just such a great moment.

350
00:17:43.984 --> 00:17:47.362
[Roberts] <i>Well. this boy is</i>
<i>on absolute fire at the moment.</i>

351
00:17:47.446 --> 00:17:50.324
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>That is</i>
<i>an impressive performance.</i>

352
00:17:50.407 --> 00:17:52.117
[Rathbone] I'm fortunate to have
an amazing family.

353
00:17:52.201 --> 00:17:53.911
My parents were
always confident in. you know.

354
00:17:53.994 --> 00:17:55.329
this is just a setback. this happens.

355
00:17:55.412 --> 00:17:58.123
Just kind of making sure
that I didn't drop my standards…

356
00:17:58.207 --> 00:17:59.708
and kind of gave everything every day.

357
00:17:59.792 --> 00:18:01.126
Because it's easy
sometimes when you think.

358
00:18:01.210 --> 00:18:02.711
"Oh. God. I'm not getting a game
at the moment

359
00:18:02.795 --> 00:18:04.505
so I'm gonna. sack it off today."

360
00:18:04.588 --> 00:18:07.341
and they kinda just made me promise like.
don't let that happen.

361
00:18:07.424 --> 00:18:09.218
Which they were absolutely spot-on to do.

362
00:18:14.556 --> 00:18:15.682
Beyond words.

363
00:18:15.766 --> 00:18:16.850
[smacks lips. stutters] Oh.

364
00:18:17.518 --> 00:18:22.022
[crowd cheers] Ollie! Ollie! Ollie!

365
00:18:22.106 --> 00:18:25.776
Ollie! Ollie! Ollie!

366
00:18:29.738 --> 00:18:31.698
Yeah. The best.

367
00:18:35.577 --> 00:18:37.538
[Gilpin] Revelation for me
over the last couple of weeks.

368
00:18:37.621 --> 00:18:38.997
and I'm really pleased for this.

369
00:18:39.081 --> 00:18:41.208
I just feel we've hit a groove
at the moment.

370
00:18:41.291 --> 00:18:44.753
[Edwards] Probably the most enjoyable
chunk of football.

371
00:18:44.837 --> 00:18:46.088
What a great. great time.

372
00:18:46.171 --> 00:18:50.801
[Harvey] We start on Boxing Day against
our old foes from Sheffield United.

373
00:18:50.884 --> 00:18:52.052
{\an8}Come on. Josh.

374
00:18:52.136 --> 00:18:55.264
{\an8}[Griffiths] Right-footed! It's 5!

375
00:18:55.347 --> 00:18:56.431
[crowd cheering]

376
00:18:56.515 --> 00:18:58.350
[laughs] Get in!

377
00:18:58.433 --> 00:19:02.855
{\an8}[Griffiths] Wrexham 5. Sheffield United 3.

378
00:19:02.938 --> 00:19:04.398
Happy Christmas.

379
00:19:04.481 --> 00:19:08.026
[Harvey] And then with Preston
and Blackburn on New Year's Day.

380
00:19:08.110 --> 00:19:10.237
which set us up for the last game
at Derby.

381
00:19:10.320 --> 00:19:11.864
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>Thomason takes a touch.</i>

382
00:19:11.947 --> 00:19:14.908
{\an8}<i>hooks it in the goalmouth.</i>
<i>good defend by Sanderson.</i>

383
00:19:14.992 --> 00:19:17.661
<i>He alters his balance well to clear.</i>

384
00:19:17.744 --> 00:19:19.496
<i>Poor clearance. though.</i>
<i>Matty James hits it!</i>

385
00:19:19.580 --> 00:19:21.915
<i>Oh. yes!</i>

386
00:19:21.999 --> 00:19:25.043
[fan] Get in! Fucking get in. lads!

387
00:19:25.127 --> 00:19:27.254
[Griffiths] <i>Is that enough</i>
<i>celebration for you?</i>

388
00:19:27.337 --> 00:19:28.922
-Yes!
-[fan 2] Come on!

389
00:19:29.006 --> 00:19:30.340
Come on!

390
00:19:30.424 --> 00:19:34.469
{\an8}[Griffiths] <i>And that is the final whistle.</i>
<i>Wrexham win at Derby.</i>

391
00:19:34.553 --> 00:19:39.308
<i>For the first time ever.</i>
<i>we've won four second tier games in a row.</i>

392
00:19:39.391 --> 00:19:43.145
[Gilpin] We are a very happy podcast
because. all of a sudden.

393
00:19:43.228 --> 00:19:45.564
we are 9th in the Championship.

394
00:19:45.647 --> 00:19:48.483
Just one point off the playoffs.

395
00:19:48.567 --> 00:19:51.361
I don't think
that going into the holiday period.

396
00:19:51.445 --> 00:19:54.698
anybody expected the team
to get 12 points.

397
00:19:54.781 --> 00:19:56.742
But equally. the players were tired.

398
00:19:56.825 --> 00:19:59.995
They haven't had a chance to recover.
yet the same players had to go again.

399
00:20:00.078 --> 00:20:01.830
[Parkinson] Come on.
let's get it going then now.

400
00:20:01.914 --> 00:20:04.917
Get it going. this group going.
Let's go. son. Good.

401
00:20:07.794 --> 00:20:10.088
In the Championship. there's 46 games.

402
00:20:10.172 --> 00:20:12.341
where the Premiership have 38 games.

403
00:20:12.424 --> 00:20:15.677
So there's a lot more midweek games.
and it's very intense.

404
00:20:15.761 --> 00:20:17.763
A lot of high-speed running.

405
00:20:17.846 --> 00:20:20.265
The sprint distance is a lot higher
than we're used to.

406
00:20:21.141 --> 00:20:23.018
It's not just gonna be.
you know. flick a switch

407
00:20:23.101 --> 00:20:25.145
and you suddenly
become a Championship player.

408
00:20:25.812 --> 00:20:28.190
You've got to work
on aspects of your game.

409
00:20:28.273 --> 00:20:30.234
The way you live.
the way you prepare for games.

410
00:20:30.317 --> 00:20:33.195
the work you do in the gym.
the work with sports science.

411
00:20:33.278 --> 00:20:36.406
some of the tactical kind of differences
in the division.

412
00:20:36.490 --> 00:20:38.200
and you've got to adapt to all those.

413
00:20:38.909 --> 00:20:42.079
[Mulholland] We don't like
to leave any stone unturned

414
00:20:42.162 --> 00:20:45.082
{\an8}in the player's performance
and hydration. nutrition

415
00:20:45.165 --> 00:20:46.375
is really. really key to that.

416
00:20:46.458 --> 00:20:48.210
It's one of the pillars
that we really focus on.

417
00:20:48.293 --> 00:20:51.088
It really helps the players
both physically and mentally

418
00:20:51.171 --> 00:20:54.174
to go the whole way to the end of games.
which is important for us.

419
00:20:54.258 --> 00:20:55.467
[Harvey] To get us to the Premier League.

420
00:20:55.550 --> 00:20:57.594
we're arguably going to have
to be more successful

421
00:20:57.678 --> 00:21:00.514
in the second half of the season.
which is difficult.

422
00:21:00.597 --> 00:21:03.850
particularly with the third round
of the FA Cup coming up

423
00:21:03.934 --> 00:21:05.394
in such a short period of time.

424
00:21:08.105 --> 00:21:11.191
{\an8}[Darren Fletcher] So welcome along
to the draw for the FA Cup third round.

425
00:21:11.275 --> 00:21:15.320
{\an8}We are live from St James's Park.
home of Brackley Town.

426
00:21:15.404 --> 00:21:17.823
<i>alongside their wonderful fans</i>
<i>in here tonight.</i>

427
00:21:17.906 --> 00:21:20.367
[fans cheering. applause]

428
00:21:21.243 --> 00:21:23.537
[Darren] <i>Right. the Premier League</i>
<i>and Championship clubs.</i>

429
00:21:23.620 --> 00:21:25.872
<i>of course. enter the competition.</i>

430
00:21:25.956 --> 00:21:28.542
<i>We're now down to 65 teams</i>

431
00:21:28.625 --> 00:21:33.755
<i>from 747 who started on the journey.</i>

432
00:21:33.839 --> 00:21:36.216
<i>Joe. you're gonna start us off</i>
<i>with the home teams.</i>

433
00:21:36.300 --> 00:21:37.718
<i>Crouchy's gonna do the away teams.</i>

434
00:21:37.801 --> 00:21:40.637
