<i>4-3 to Wrexham.</i>

493
00:24:30.765 --> 00:24:32.350
<i>The last penalty of the ten.</i>

494
00:24:34.769 --> 00:24:37.981
-[cheering]
-[Griffiths] <i>Saved! Wrexham are through!</i>

495
00:24:38.523 --> 00:24:42.152
{\an8}<i>Arthur Okonkwo. the hero.</i>
<i>diving to his left!</i>

496
00:24:42.235 --> 00:24:46.114
I've trained and played my whole life
to create moments like that.

497
00:24:46.198 --> 00:24:48.241
to-to be a hero in a penalty shoot-out.

498
00:24:48.325 --> 00:24:50.285
So yeah. it's a moment I'll never forget.

499
00:24:50.368 --> 00:24:52.496
-[people shouting]
-[patron] Big Arthur!

500
00:24:52.579 --> 00:24:54.956
[Mac] Anyway. it went really well.

501
00:24:55.040 --> 00:24:58.376
And that night.
I was with all of my Philly friends.

502
00:24:58.460 --> 00:25:01.046
which meant I got really drunk.

503
00:25:01.838 --> 00:25:04.925
[narrator]
<i>We earnt our swagger and proved our worth.</i>

504
00:25:05.008 --> 00:25:07.260
<i>Giving the fans a reason for mirth.</i>

505
00:25:07.928 --> 00:25:10.514
<i>Though the forest loomed</i>
<i>imposing and tall.</i>

506
00:25:10.597 --> 00:25:14.851
<i>Wrexham rose up.</i>
<i>causing their opponents to fall.</i>

507
00:25:14.935 --> 00:25:17.604
[crowd vocalizing]

508
00:25:17.687 --> 00:25:18.980
Wrexham!

509
00:25:26.196 --> 00:25:28.156
{\an8}-[person 1] Hi. guys.
-[person 2] Hello.

510
00:25:28.240 --> 00:25:30.283
[person 1] The Wrexham shop
luckily gave us

511
00:25:30.367 --> 00:25:34.412
nine T-shirts to do a snood workshop.

512
00:25:34.496 --> 00:25:37.415
These tops. don't even worry
about cutting them up

513
00:25:37.499 --> 00:25:39.751
because it's tops
that would've gone into landfill.

514
00:25:39.834 --> 00:25:44.047
So see. on the back of that one.
the vinyl has all come off.

515
00:25:44.130 --> 00:25:45.215
So they can't sell that.

516
00:25:45.298 --> 00:25:48.051
They've given 'em us for this.

517
00:25:52.514 --> 00:25:55.809
I'm Gemma Oakley.
and I run Wrexham Sewing Studio.

518
00:25:58.645 --> 00:26:01.606
So. we're just gonna go
a little bit further over. That's it.

519
00:26:02.649 --> 00:26:03.692
Oh. she's on it.

520
00:26:04.276 --> 00:26:06.987
♪ <i>Over the hill. just down the road </i>♪

521
00:26:08.071 --> 00:26:11.116
♪ <i>There's a place. I loved it though</i> ♪

522
00:26:11.199 --> 00:26:14.160
This is a safe space
for people to come in.

523
00:26:14.244 --> 00:26:16.162
learn something that they didn't know.

524
00:26:16.246 --> 00:26:18.206
It's just somewhere you can go

525
00:26:18.290 --> 00:26:21.167
where you don't have to worry
about your day-to-day life.

526
00:26:21.251 --> 00:26:22.794
apart from me being in it.

527
00:26:23.670 --> 00:26:26.673
causing absolute carnage wherever I go.

528
00:26:29.593 --> 00:26:33.388
I've been doing voluntary groups
for about four years

529
00:26:33.471 --> 00:26:35.932
because I've got a colorful past.

530
00:26:43.523 --> 00:26:47.235
My whole life has
been drink. drugs. fighting.

531
00:26:59.623 --> 00:27:00.999
And I didn't go to prison.

532
00:27:01.082 --> 00:27:05.086
So. so close. though.
and that was a turning point. really.

533
00:27:06.212 --> 00:27:07.547
-[Gemma's child] Mum.
-What. mate?

534
00:27:07.631 --> 00:27:10.091
-I can get you some cobblestone.
-What you gonna build? What about a house?

535
00:27:10.175 --> 00:27:11.760
Shall I build the house with the bricks?

536
00:27:11.843 --> 00:27:17.307
[Gemma] Now. I look back and I think
I'm glad that I've done all of that stuff.

537
00:27:17.390 --> 00:27:22.312
because I'm in a good place now
where I can say to people. "Don't do it.

538
00:27:22.395 --> 00:27:27.025
Do something else. craft.
or… just do something different."

539
00:27:27.108 --> 00:27:30.737
[person 1] I remember when Gem was
participating in the classes.

540
00:27:30.820 --> 00:27:35.408
{\an8}and then. obviously. she learned
her skills. she did her courses.

541
00:27:35.492 --> 00:27:38.161
{\an8}Like. you see how much she's smashed life

542
00:27:38.244 --> 00:27:40.038
and it's to be able
to show other people now.

543
00:27:40.121 --> 00:27:42.666
-"If Gemma can do it. you can do it."
-[Gemma] Yeah. yeah.

544
00:27:43.375 --> 00:27:47.545
[Gemma] I'd just say sewing's changed
my life. like. it's given me structure.

545
00:27:47.629 --> 00:27:49.339
It's given me confidence.

546
00:27:50.465 --> 00:27:52.425
And I want to give it back

547
00:27:53.051 --> 00:27:56.680
to help others
that are in the same position as me.

548
00:27:56.763 --> 00:28:01.351
So this is a Wrexham bear
out of upcycled materials.

549
00:28:02.394 --> 00:28:05.271
I got the idea from the bears
from a lady downstairs.

550
00:28:05.355 --> 00:28:08.274
She told me. "You need to get
one of them bears to Ryan Reynolds."

551
00:28:08.358 --> 00:28:12.487
[chuckling] And I was like.
"You. my friend. are a little superstar."

552
00:28:12.570 --> 00:28:17.784
{\an8}So we are going to take them over
to Mike in the Wrexham shop.

553
00:28:17.867 --> 00:28:22.038
