648
00:32:45.802 --> 00:32:47.887
{\an8}[Roberts]
Wrexham just weathered the storm.

649
00:32:47.971 --> 00:32:50.640
[Griffiths] Zero shots at half time. Ouch.

650
00:32:50.723 --> 00:32:55.061
Can Wrexham turn in
an improved second half performance?

651
00:32:55.144 --> 00:32:56.938
I mean. we need to.

652
00:32:57.772 --> 00:33:00.692
{\an8}[Roberts] Wrexham going
into the second half a lot more fresher.

653
00:33:00.775 --> 00:33:04.362
You know. they know now
what QPR's game plan is.

654
00:33:05.238 --> 00:33:08.116
[Griffiths] Right-footed.
delivers an inswinger into a good area.

655
00:33:08.199 --> 00:33:11.536
Hits the bar. and Okonkwo does well
to catch the rebound.

656
00:33:11.619 --> 00:33:14.372
[Roberts] Arthur Okonkwo. really not
been tested in this second half.

657
00:33:14.455 --> 00:33:16.582
[Morrell] But at some point.
Wrexham are gonna have to go in

658
00:33:16.666 --> 00:33:17.917
a little bit stronger.

659
00:33:18.001 --> 00:33:21.212
[Griffiths] Here's Okonkwo now.
Drilling it through the middle.

660
00:33:21.295 --> 00:33:24.590
That's a hell of a ball for Broadhead.
left side of the area.

661
00:33:24.674 --> 00:33:26.384
He breaks onto it. Moore's inside.

662
00:33:26.467 --> 00:33:29.178
Broadhead takes on his man.
Good tackle by Dunne.

663
00:33:29.262 --> 00:33:30.388
And the shot comes in!

664
00:33:30.471 --> 00:33:31.931
-Hell of a save by the keeper.
-[groans]

665
00:33:32.974 --> 00:33:35.643
Here's Broadhead now. feeding a good ball
to Doyle on the overlap.

666
00:33:35.727 --> 00:33:36.978
Hits the shot!

667
00:33:37.061 --> 00:33:40.398
And scores his first goal for Wrexham!
A screamer!

668
00:33:40.481 --> 00:33:43.943
{\an8}Tight angle. but it was on his left foot
and he's going nuts!

669
00:33:44.027 --> 00:33:46.612
{\an8}Punching the air
in front of the Wrexham fans!

670
00:33:46.696 --> 00:33:50.199
[Roberts] Wrexham. just felt like suddenly
turned up the intensity times ten.

671
00:33:50.283 --> 00:33:51.284
Game on.

672
00:33:52.160 --> 00:33:55.663
[Griffiths] Broadhead is coming off now
for Rathbone to come on.

673
00:33:55.747 --> 00:33:58.082
We need to turn on the attack mode.

674
00:33:58.166 --> 00:34:01.502
Enter Rathbone.
so I think his energy can be very helpful.

675
00:34:01.586 --> 00:34:03.421
[chanting] Ollie! Ollie! Ollie!

676
00:34:03.504 --> 00:34:08.384
[Roberts] Rathbone coming off the bench
and going. "No. we want the win here."

677
00:34:08.468 --> 00:34:10.720
[Griffiths] To float it
towards the near post! What a header!

678
00:34:10.803 --> 00:34:14.432
What a goal! And QPR catch Wrexham out.

679
00:34:14.515 --> 00:34:18.978
{\an8}It's across Okonkwo.
and Wrexham go behind again.

680
00:34:20.938 --> 00:34:25.860
Frustration for Wrexham after turning
this game round so effectively.

681
00:34:25.943 --> 00:34:29.781
[Roberts] QPR just turned the screw again.
getting on those second balls.

682
00:34:29.864 --> 00:34:34.118
-[Griffiths] Windass is ready to come on.
-[chanting] Wrexham! Wrexham!

683
00:34:35.453 --> 00:34:37.747
[Griffiths] Feeds it to the edge
of the area. Hayden tries to curl it.

684
00:34:37.830 --> 00:34:40.541
Puts it over.
It's QPR now with the wind in their sails.

685
00:34:40.625 --> 00:34:42.126
[Morrell] Putting more pressure
on the Wrexham players.

686
00:34:42.210 --> 00:34:43.878
[Griffiths] Plays the big diagonal.

687
00:34:43.961 --> 00:34:45.505
Looking for Moore.
who heads it down beautifully.

688
00:34:45.588 --> 00:34:48.007
O'Brien is there.
Poor touch. Lays it back.

689
00:34:48.091 --> 00:34:50.802
Shot comes and it's blocked.
O'Brien. Windass again.

690
00:34:50.885 --> 00:34:53.262
-It ricochets into the keeper's hands.
-Fucking hell!

691
00:34:55.473 --> 00:34:56.974
[Griffiths] With time running down.

692
00:34:57.058 --> 00:34:59.519
their hope of getting a place
in a playoff spot

693
00:34:59.602 --> 00:35:01.312
might have to wait a little longer.

694
00:35:01.395 --> 00:35:02.730
[chanting] Wrexham! Wrexham!

695
00:35:02.814 --> 00:35:05.483
[Griffiths] I can't believe
there's only four minutes of added time.

696
00:35:05.566 --> 00:35:08.569
I've got to say. especially in a game
which has twisted and turned.

697
00:35:09.237 --> 00:35:12.323
Yeah. Wrexham really need
to dig in and get through this.

698
00:35:12.406 --> 00:35:14.075
Just relax. everybody. a bit!

699
00:35:14.158 --> 00:35:16.494
[Griffiths]
Rathbone lays it off. desperate stuff.

700
00:35:16.577 --> 00:35:20.164
Windass. long range shot. good power.
Good save by the keeper.

701
00:35:21.124 --> 00:35:23.209
Inswinging corner
from the right-hand side.

702
00:35:23.292 --> 00:35:24.961
O'Brien is on it. He signals.

703
00:35:25.920 --> 00:35:28.798
Sweeps it under the bar.
Keeper comes. punches one-handed.

704
00:35:28.881 --> 00:35:35.221
{\an8}It's driven in! What a finish by Windass!
It bounced so high. but he didn't care!

705
00:35:35.304 --> 00:35:40.434
{\an8}He volleys it in! Oh. that's…
That's a hit and a half. isn't it?

706
00:35:40.518 --> 00:35:44.147
[Morrell] Technique.
What a… [chuckles] What a hit.

707
00:35:44.230 --> 00:35:48.693
'Cause that bounce is up near his waist.
but he gets his body outside of the ball

708
00:35:48.776 --> 00:35:51.445
and he hits down on it.
which keeps it down.

709
00:35:51.529 --> 00:35:55.283
Arrowed across
and flies into the roof of the net.

710
00:35:56.242 --> 00:35:57.743
No celebration.

711
00:35:57.827 --> 00:35:59.996
Annoyed that he's not starting
this football match.

712
00:36:00.079 --> 00:36:02.874
But still. what a hit.

713
00:36:03.541 --> 00:36:06.294
[chanting]
Who are ya? Who are ya? Who are ya?

714
00:36:10.256 --> 00:36:11.257
Wrexham!

715
00:36:13.092 --> 00:36:16.179
[Roberts] Brilliant technique.
You felt like QPR were just cracking.

716
00:36:16.262 --> 00:36:18.389
They'll be so frustrated not to cling on.

717
00:36:18.472 --> 00:36:20.391
[Parkinson]
Come on. keep us going! Come on!

718
00:36:20.474 --> 00:36:22.310
Just under a minute probably left
in this game.

719
00:36:22.393 --> 00:36:23.853
-Are we gonna see a winner?
-[Morrell] Go for the win.

720
00:36:23.936 --> 00:36:25.396
[Parkinson] Get up to the ball!

721
00:36:26.272 --> 00:36:28.858
[chanting] Wrexham! Wrexham! Wrexham!

722
00:36:28.941 --> 00:36:30.401
[Griffiths] Now a draw won't do.

723
00:36:30.484 --> 00:36:33.112
Wrexham need a win
to get into that playoff spot.

724
00:36:34.780 --> 00:36:38.868
Now here. Wrexham are pushing on again.
O'Brien helps it wide.

725
00:36:38.951 --> 00:36:41.370
And it's Windass driving
down the left-hand side.

726
00:36:42.121 --> 00:36:44.749
Fed back to Doyle.
Doyle chips into the box.

727
00:36:44.832 --> 00:36:48.836
There's a scramble. and Kolli just
smashes it to the halfway line.

728
00:36:48.920 --> 00:36:50.838
Boy. oh. boy.

729
00:36:50.922 --> 00:36:55.009
Rathbone now. whips it into the box
and its attack… Drops loose!

730
00:36:55.092 --> 00:36:58.012
Moore is there. can't quite get there.
It's hacked away.

731
00:36:58.095 --> 00:37:00.097
Rathbone. Constant this.

732
00:37:00.181 --> 00:37:02.266
We've got nine seconds left
of the four added minutes.

733
00:37:02.350 --> 00:37:05.019
Ref should add another minute on.
Rathbone long-ranger.

734
00:37:06.103 --> 00:37:10.650
Oh. my! Oh. my word!
What a goal by Rathbone!

735
00:37:10.733 --> 00:37:12.443
I love that man!

736
00:37:12.526 --> 00:37:15.905
{\an8}Ollie Rathbone. have my children!
Please. take them!

737
00:37:15.988 --> 00:37:18.115
{\an8}Oh… [stutters] Sorry. Ben.

738
00:37:18.199 --> 00:37:21.410
[stammers] You can't go with Ollie.
Oh. my God. though.

739
00:37:21.494 --> 00:37:23.913
["Hallelujah" playing]

740
00:37:24.538 --> 00:37:27.208
You know. as a young lad
that's loved football all his life.

741
00:37:27.291 --> 00:37:30.002
you kind of literally grow up
picturing that moment.

742
00:37:30.753 --> 00:37:33.881
To be the one fortunate enough
to score the winner is

743
00:37:33.965 --> 00:37:35.633
just everything I've ever dreamed of.

744
00:37:37.009 --> 00:37:39.720
Okonkwo is up there
at the away end celebrating!

745
00:37:39.804 --> 00:37:42.640
Ollie Rathbone! Ollie Rathbone.

746
00:37:42.723 --> 00:37:45.726
{\an8}[Morrell] Well. I'm nearly
on Ollie Rathbone's back as well in here.

747
00:37:45.810 --> 00:37:48.145
{\an8}because that is sensational.

748
00:37:48.229 --> 00:37:51.899
[Roberts]
QPR. what a disaster. but who cares?

749
00:37:51.983 --> 00:37:55.653
Ollie Rathbone. yet again.
off the bench with a goal.

750
00:37:56.445 --> 00:37:57.446
Impact.

751
00:37:59.156 --> 00:38:02.368
[narrator] <i>Wrexham in a playoff spot.</i>
<i>now who could believe?</i>

752
00:38:02.451 --> 00:38:06.455
A <i>holiday miracle</i>
<i>that only hope could conceive.</i>

753
00:38:07.039 --> 00:38:08.582
That's a fucking huge win for us today.

754
00:38:08.666 --> 00:38:10.710
It gets us right in the fucking mix
and do you know what?

755
00:38:10.793 --> 00:38:12.461
It's because we've got
a fucking good team.

756
00:38:12.545 --> 00:38:14.338
We're in the playoff positions.

757
00:38:14.422 --> 00:38:17.508
We're in the playoff positions.
Who would ever believe it?

758
00:38:17.591 --> 00:38:20.094
Going through that is probably…

759
00:38:20.177 --> 00:38:22.471
My cardiologist will probably
have words to say to me.

760
00:38:22.555 --> 00:38:24.181
but now I am just delighted.

761
00:38:24.265 --> 00:38:27.018
♪ <i>Oh. Ollie Rathbone</i>
<i>You are the love of my life</i> ♪

762
00:38:27.101 --> 00:38:30.604
♪ <i>Oh. Ollie Rathbone</i>
<i>I'd let you shag my wife</i> ♪

763
00:38:30.688 --> 00:38:32.481
♪ <i>Oh. Ollie Rathbone</i> ♪

764
00:38:33.065 --> 00:38:35.318
I couldn't put it better myself.
to be honest.

765
00:38:35.401 --> 00:38:36.861
That… That's about it. really.

766
00:38:36.944 --> 00:38:40.281
-[Christmas bells jingling]
-[♪ festive music plays]

767
00:38:45.036 --> 00:38:48.039
{\an8}Football and-and Christmas in the UK
just go hand in hand. don't they?

768
00:38:48.122 --> 00:38:51.667
{\an8}They just… Everybody's up for it.
everybody's in the pub celebrating.

769
00:38:51.751 --> 00:38:54.628
Just to see grown adults in tears
because they're happy.

770
00:38:54.712 --> 00:38:58.257
And kids. and-and I couldn't believe.
like. how lucky we are as a town.

771
00:38:58.341 --> 00:39:00.509
and how lucky I am
as a local little business owner.

772
00:39:00.593 --> 00:39:04.013
And I get teary. I get emotional.
just like a Christmas morning.

773
00:39:04.096 --> 00:39:05.139
because you think. you know.

774
00:39:05.222 --> 00:39:07.600
I'm just like tens of thousands
of other Wrexham fans.

775
00:39:07.683 --> 00:39:09.560
That's all we are. is we're fans.
we put our money in.

776
00:39:09.643 --> 00:39:11.687
and we go in the hope
that we're gonna win football games.

777
00:39:11.771 --> 00:39:14.607
Life really couldn't get much better.
could it. as a Wrexham fan. you know?

778
00:39:15.608 --> 00:39:19.320
[narrator] <i>Wrexham's rise.</i>
<i>a second chance that burns like a flame.</i>

779
00:39:19.403 --> 00:39:23.324
<i>Not just in the pitch.</i>
<i>but in the hearts that bear its name.</i>

780
00:39:23.407 --> 00:39:24.992
[laughing]

781
00:39:25.076 --> 00:39:28.704
<i>For the people of Wrexham</i>
<i>who struggle and persevere.</i>

782
00:39:28.788 --> 00:39:33.793
<i>Find hope in a comeback</i>
<i>that only comes this time of year.</i>

783
00:39:33.876 --> 00:39:35.461
[♪ festive music continues]

784
00:39:41.175 --> 00:39:42.259
{\an8}[♪ music ends]

785
00:39:43.305 --> 00:40:43.916
